    <span class="pres-overline pres-reveal" style="color: var(--pres-blue-500);">THE CHALLENGE</span>
    <h2 class="pres-reveal pres-reveal-delay-1">AI Without a Control Center</h2>
    <div class="pres-divider pres-reveal pres-reveal-delay-1"></div>
    <div class="pres-row" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <div class="pres-col-half pres-reveal pres-reveal-delay-2">
        <h3 style="color: var(--pres-blue-700); margin-bottom: 1rem;">What Your Teams Need</h3>
        <ul class="pres-features">
          <li><strong>Access to AI skills</strong> &mdash; domain-specific knowledge that makes AI useful for their role</li>
          <li><strong>Self-service install</strong> &mdash; browse, select, and install skills into Claude without waiting for IT</li>
          <li><strong>Admin visibility</strong> &mdash; leadership needs to see who is using AI, how, and at what cost</li>
          <li><strong>Non-technical access</strong> &mdash; staff who are not developers need easily accessible skills without technical barriers</li>
          <li><strong>IT control</strong> &mdash; govern what gets deployed, who can access it, and what data flows where</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="pres-col-half pres-reveal pres-reveal-delay-3">
        <h3 style="color: var(--pres-red); margin-bottom: 1rem;">What Is Missing Today</h3>
        <ul class="pres-features">
          <li><strong>No central management</strong> &mdash; skills and AI capabilities are scattered across teams and tools</li>
          <li><strong>No usage visibility</strong> &mdash; no one knows which teams use AI, how much it costs, or what tools are called</li>
          <li><strong>No personalization</strong> &mdash; every team gets the same generic AI, none of your domain expertise is captured</li>
          <li><strong>No non-technical path</strong> &mdash; existing AI tooling assumes technical users, leaving most of the organization behind</li>
          <li><strong>No self-service onboarding</strong> &mdash; every new user requires manual setup and configuration</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
