  <div class="pres-notes">
    <div class="note-section"><h4>TIMING: 1:00 &mdash; The Problem (90s)</h4><p><strong>Say:</strong> "Your teams need access to AI skills that are specific to their domain. They need to be able to install those skills themselves, without an IT ticket, without a deployment pipeline. And critically, non-technical staff need a path that does not require developer expertise."</p><p><strong>Say:</strong> "Leadership needs visibility. Who is using AI? How much does it cost? What tools are being called? Right now, that data does not exist in one place."</p><p><strong>Say:</strong> "And IT needs control. What gets deployed, who can access it, what data flows where. Today, that is fragmented across teams. You need a Control Center."</p></div>
